      "detail": "Licensed availability means the data owner licenses specific computational use while retaining full custody through the confidential compute architecture. The licence permits processing but architecturally prevents the processor from accessing the underlying data directly. This is the most precise form of data licensing because the terms are enforced by technology rather than contract alone. Licensed availability with architectural enforcement demonstrates the commercial potential of use-without-custody arrangements."
